---
layout: about
permalink: /updates/
title: "Updates"
description: >-
  What we've shipped, in reverse chronological order. This page reads from
  the project's own git history, so what you see here is what's actually
  tagged.
canonical: updates/
date: 2026-05-29
---

{% if updates and updates.length > 0 %}

{% for entry in updates %}
<article id="{{ entry.tag }}" style="--mb:3rem;">
  <header>
    <h2 style="--mb:0.25rem;">
      <a href="#{{ entry.tag }}" style="--td:none;">{{ entry.tag }}</a>
    </h2>
    {% if entry.title and entry.title != entry.tag %}
    <p style="--mt:0; --mb:0.5rem; --fw:500;">{{ entry.title }}</p>
    {% endif %}
    <p style="--mt:0; --opacity:0.6; --fs:0.875rem;">
      <time datetime="{{ entry.date | htmlDateString }}">{{ entry.date | readableDate }}</time>
      &middot; <code>{{ entry.commit }}</code>
    </p>
  </header>
  {% if entry.body %}
  <div>
    {{ entry.body | md | safe }}
  </div>
  {% endif %}
</article>
{% endfor %}

<p style="--mt:4rem; --opacity:0.6; --fs:0.875rem;">
  Subscribe to the <a href="/updates.xml">Atom feed</a> to follow along.
</p>

{% else %}

<p>No releases tagged yet. When we ship a new version, it'll show up here.</p>

{% endif %}
